title: How have outpatients' experiences changed over time?
analysis_commentary: This indicator suggests that outpatients in England had a positive experience of outpatient care in 2011, a score of 79.5 out of 100 (where 0 is the worst score and 100 is the best score), which was a slight improvement from the 2009 score of 78.6 out of 100.
data_source: Health & Social Care Information Centre, Outcomes Framework Indicator Portal
